        "description": "<p><strong>sscCdi</strong> is the Coherent Diffraction Imaging package of the Sirius Scientific Computing (ssc) group.&nbsp;</p>\n<div>It currently performs:</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Ptychography</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>- Ptycho-tomography pre-processing (sorting, cropping, unwrapping, phase-ramp removal)</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>High-level level functionality is written in Python. Some of the algorithms are accelerated using C++/CUDA.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>If you have any questions, contact: <strong>gcc@lnls.br</strong></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><strong>Usage</strong></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>See examples folder for Python notebooks that show how to use package.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<p><strong>Acknowledgements</strong></p>\n<p>We would like to acknowledge the Brazilian Ministry of Science, Technology, and Innovation MCTI for supporting this work through the Brazilian Center for Research in Energy and Materials (CNPEM).</p>",
